nguage=EN>Nestie</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered Patron</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>3/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>5:09:12 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Of humble beginnings....</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Leche sat outside of the Wall in Misty Thicket...<br>
<br>
The Halfling sat outside of the wall, away from the watchful eyes of the Deputies... She sat rubbing her wounds she had just obtained from a bear, goblin, and wolf attacking her all at once...<br>
<br>
&quot;I wish I was stronger&quot; sighed the Halfling. &quot;I bet Fricka wouldn't have gotten hurt by those nasty things!&quot;<br>
<br>
The Halfling pondered as she rubbed her wounds... 'To be a like a norseman or woman...' she thought....<br>
<br>
Leche's mother had been a protective one, for she did not want her daughter growing up to be an adventurer. Her father had been a famous Wanderer of Rivervale, yet like so many of the Halfling adventurers, had died at the hands of Barbarians. <br>
<br>
The mighty Barbarians of the North had organized a large raid on the protected thicket. Leche's father died in battle against them, as did many of the brave men and women of her town. The Barbarian's were too powerful for the little Halflings.<br>
<br>
Leche born soon after the raid. Her mother brought her up to be careful as best as a mother could by telling stories to the young Halfling of evil races that wandered Norrath, the evil that had spread through the land, and the horrible barbarians that had killed her father. Leche's mother watched from afar as the raid went on. The tales were meant to scare poor Leche out of adventurering, yet they each one brought more and more intrigue to the young Halfling. Often, before going to bed, she would wonder if one day she would be as strong as the Barbarian assassin named Karne, the one who was said to have punched a Halfling through one of their burrows. Or maybe she would grow up to be like Wotan or Ghoull, two Oracles of the norsemen's guild. Maybe she would someday be as fierce and powerful as Isildur, a barbarian champion. Or even maybe... she would be like Fricka, one of the rare female barbarians that was as powerful and sneaky as the other male barbarians, if not more so. <br>
<br>
This is how early on, Leche decided that she would someday be like Fricka, master thief and assassin that proudly represents her people. She would take a bit of her mother's stories into mind, that Elves were evil and out for your money, Humans wanted nothing more than your soul to offer to their pagan gods, and the Dark races... the Dark races would eat you if you weren't careful. She would someday learn to steal from the ones too tall, to kill the frail elves, to evade the hungry evil races.<br>
<br>
Leche stood up from the wall, her wounds no longer bothering her. She grasped her dagger, and went out, deep into the thicket...<br>
